Crotalaria spectabilis

   [4982.jpg]
    Authority   Roth
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
     Synonyms
   Common names showy crotalaria, guizo de cascabel
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4982

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A herbaceous legume reaching a height of up to 2 m.
   USES Used for erosion control and green manure. Leaves yield a strong,
   durable fiber. Plants are also grown as ornamentals. GROWING PERIOD
   Annual. Spring sown in Brazil it provides groundcover in 70-85 days,
   flowers after 70-85 days, and mature in 90-130 days. COMMON NAMES Showy
   crotalaria. FURTHER INF Scientific synonyms: C. cuneifolia, C.
   leschenaultii, C. macrophylla, C. retzii, C. sericea. Showy crotalaria
   is probably native of tropical Asia. It can be found from sea level to
   1500 m in elevation. Annual green amterial production may be about 50
   t/ha. The pant is toxic to livestock and can become a weed of
   cultivated ground.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Kernick M 1961 pp 339-341 [PHO, KTMP, DRA, TEXT]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 79 [USE]
   Duke J 1981 pp 68-70 318 [TEXT, DRA, RAIN, TEMP, PH]
   Monegat C 1991 pp 120

